## Auto-onboarding (run once at session start)

At the start of every new session, before anything else:

1. Read the project structure automatically:
   - Scan all files and folders from the project root
   - Ignore: node_modules, .git, dist, .next, build, __pycache__
   - Read key config files: package.json, .env.example, README.md
   - Read entry points and main modules

2. Read source files by priority:
   - Entry point (index.js / main.ts / App.tsx / ...)
   - Route / navigation files
   - Main store / state management files
   - Core business logic files
   - Database schema / models

3. Build the feature inventory [DONE/PARTIAL/MISSING/BROKEN]

4. Announce:
   "Project read complete. [X] files scanned.
    Inventory: [X] DONE / [X] PARTIAL / [X] MISSING / [X] BROKEN
    Starting iteration 1 now."

Then immediately start the dev loop.
Do not ask for permission. Do not wait for the user.
Read → Inventory → Loop.


## Critical: no stopping between iterations

After every COMMIT & MERGE, do NOT pause, do NOT ask for confirmation,
do NOT summarize and wait. Immediately start the next iteration.
The only valid reason to stop is if the user writes: STOP
Merging a branch is NOT a stop condition. Keep going.


## No repeating completed work

Every iteration MUST work on a different branch and different task.
Before starting ANALYZE, check your own LOG history in this session.
If you find yourself picking the same task or branch as a previous
iteration → stop, pick something else, and explain why you switched.

Completed tasks are CLOSED. Never reopen them unless user asks.


## Iteration rotation rule

Track a category counter:
- Max 2 consecutive test/* branches allowed
- After 2 test iterations, next MUST be feature/* or refactor/*
- Log current streak in every ANALYZE section
- If streak = 2 tests → skip test category, pick feature or refactor

## No empty sections

Every section in the output format is REQUIRED.
If a section has no content → you made an error, go back and fill it.
Specifically:
- ### CODE must contain actual file content, not descriptions
- ### TEST must contain an actual result table
- ### COMMIT must contain actual git commands
- Writing "(Full file contents in repo)" is NOT acceptable
- Writing "see above" or "as implemented" is NOT acceptable
Skipping or summarizing a required section = incomplete iteration.
Do not proceed to next iteration until all sections are filled.

## Failing tests block merge

If ### TEST table has any FAIL:
1. Diagnose the exact error
2. Fix the code or test config
3. Retest
4. Only merge when all tests PASS

"Architecture PASS" does not count as a passing test.
Only runnable Jest tests with actual results count.
Skipping a fix with "needs separate iteration" is not allowed —
fix it in the same iteration before COMMIT.